description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an opportunity for an Anesthetic Practitioner to work in Anesthetics and 1 other perioperative area, Recovery, Admissions and Discharges or Scrub. We are looking for a Theatre Practitioner with the relevant skills and qualifications for theatres, who is looking to work in a friendly and supportive team, with a number of development opportunities within the Manchester Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen in our TDC theatre department. The unit caters for adult and paediatric inpatient and ambulatory day case patients undergoing procedures with general anaesthesia and regional block.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The unit houses the North West regional Plastic Surgery specialty, and is a leading Hand Trauma Centre and is also the leading European hospital for tendon reconstruction. The department also provides Major Breast reconstruction and Ortho/Plastic services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are at the forefront of staff development, with our dedicated in house leadership framework, and have a wealth of development opportunities available to all staff, including;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Theatre Specific Training&lt;br /&gt;Coaching&lt;br /&gt;Preceptorship Programme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;LEAD Leadership and Management sessions including:&lt;br /&gt;• Understanding and Developing Emotional Resilience&lt;br /&gt;• Understanding Stress&lt;br /&gt;• Assertiveness &lt;br /&gt;• Challenging Conversations &lt;br /&gt;• Understanding Change – Learn how to be change ready&lt;br /&gt;• Take Control of Your Time&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are a multidisciplinary team, who work closely together and support each other, whilst providing high quality peri-operative care to all our patients. This area is a dynamic department, pushing the frontiers of medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
